techmeme.title: Anysphere debuts a $200/month Ultra plan for Cursor with 20x more usage on AI models from OpenAI, Anthropic, Google DeepMind, and xAI vs. its $20/month Pro plan (Maxwell Zeff/TechCrunch)
Threads launches a fediverse feed and a way to search for fediverse users, with support for Mastodon and others, for users who turned on fediverse sharing (David Pierce/The Verge)
Waymo expands its coverage area in San Francisco and LA by 80 square miles each, bringing its total coverage area in California to 250 square miles (Andrew J. Hawkins/The Verge)
Google makes Gemini 2.5 Flash and Pro generally available and introduces 2.5 Flash-Lite, which it says is its most cost-efficient and fastest 2.5 model yet (Tulsee Doshi/The Keyword)
Salesforce says it will increase prices on many products in August, including Slack; major product lines will see a 6% increase on average (Brody Ford/Bloomberg)
